    producer: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention
    title: Drug Overdose Deaths in the US
    description: |-
      The National Center for Health Statistics (NCHS) at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention collects information on deaths involving drugs commonly associated with fatal overdose. This information is available in a searchable database called CDC WONDER (Wide-ranging Online Data for Epidemiologic Research).

      CDC WONDER allows users to query mortality data from death certificates filed in US states and the District of Columbia, including counts and rates for drug overdose deaths by year, demographic group, and other characteristics.
    title_snapshot: Drug Overdose Deaths in the US - CDC WONDER
